{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013nCSqLZhydi8t4PN5hS3uZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only es-0 is running but not ready after 10 minutes. Only one pod has started - the StatefulSet creates pods one at a time, and pods 1 and 2 haven't started yet. Also the readiness probe is failing. Let me check what's happening.\n\nPossible issues:\n1. Only one pod (es-0) started - StatefulSet creates pods sequentially, only starts es-1 after es-0 is ready. But es-0 can't become ready because it can't form a cluster without es-1 and es-2 (due to cluster.initial_master_nodes requiring all 3).\n2. This is a classic chicken-and-egg problem - the readiness probe checks cluster health, but the cluster won't be healthy until all 3 nodes join, so es-0 can't become Ready and es-1 never starts.\n\nI can fix this by either allowing all pods to start in parallel instead of sequentially, or by changing the readiness probe to just verify the node is responding rather than checking full cluster health. I'll update the StatefulSet to use parallel pod management and adjust the readiness probe accordingly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1993,"cache_read_input_tokens":36389,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1993},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7cc2bc1-d1ae-4b8c-ae09-e1ca7d9cdcd8","uuid":"318bf072-52b3-4c0c-8243-58d048437b45","request_id":"req_011CcfDZCrHNHuEnY3FmutsF"}
