{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NzqccjabBAU8tpvamo6JGX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created:**\n\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| ConfigMap | `es-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` with TLS + security config |\n| Service (Headless) | `es-transport` | Pod-to-pod discovery on port 9300 (`publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) |\n| Service (ClusterIP) | `es-http` | HTTPS access on port 9200 |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `es-pdb` | Ensures ≥2 nodes stay up during disruptions |\n| StatefulSet | `es` | 3-node cluster, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` |\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — all 3 pods start simultaneously; sequential startup causes a DNS deadlock since ES won't become Ready until the cluster forms, and the cluster can't form until all nodes can resolve each other\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on `es-transport` — without this, CoreDNS only creates records for Ready pods, which also breaks bootstrap\n- Transport TLS uses `verification_mode: certificate` since the existing cert's SANs (`*.elasticsearch.svc`) don't cover pod FQDNs\n- Password set via `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var from the pre-existing `elastic-password` secret"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":352,"cache_read_input_tokens":51101,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":352},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7cc2bc1-d1ae-4b8c-ae09-e1ca7d9cdcd8","uuid":"496f4227-7c7b-48d4-b09a-da98b89bd059","request_id":"req_011CcfEXLAdGLdExJETZ93ou"}
